node.text:
Video tour of The Syshaus designed by @studio.arthurcasas.

The Syshaus is the future of housing. It is a concept with constructive system with a standardized 1.2m grid system that allows the house to be built within 6 months. The keywords are quality, practicality, and sustainability, and eliminates the hassle of constructing a house.

node.text:
Perched atop a hill overlooking the village of Healdsburg, the Sonoma Wine Country home offers a great social space that is ideal for entertainment while maintaining the privacy of a rural retreat. “Our client was looking for us to help him create a retreat where he could get away f rom the Bay Area. He wanted a beautiful but simple modern house that was in harmony with the site and maximized indoor-outdoor living. The client worked for a tech company in San Francisco and was, at the time, a bachelor who loved modern architecture. When he originally purchased the 40 acre property, there was just a mobile home on the site – giving our team a massive amount of creativity to design a secluded retreat nestled into to the beautiful landscaping”, architect Jonathan Feldman says. The house is designed by @feldmanarchitecture. // Photos by @joefletcherphoto.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥
Link in bio!

node.text:
Swipe left! Dope or nope? 🖤
The Sky Point Villa is a yet-to-be-build home for a family of three. With its sloped roof and according skylights, the home stands out visually while giving the illusion of being truly connected to the green surrounding environment. The concept is designed and visualized by @mohtashami_reza for a plot in Bedford Hills, New York.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥

node.text:
Swipe left! What do you think? 🤔
The BT House is a corner lot home primarily built in rough concrete. In the form of an “L”, the house embraces the central garden from the outside towards the inside and the two tropical courtyards ensure that the arrival at the house is spectacular. It is designed by @jorgelina.tortorici.arq and is located in Adrogué, Argentina // Photos by @alejandroperalphotography.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥
Link in bio!

node.text:
Describe this cabin in ONE word! 😍
‘Cabin at Longbranch’ is a cabin nestled among tall fir trees in an old forest with views overlooking a beautiful lake. Designed as a set of pavilions and rustic interior, the retreat is perfect as a weekend home. The cabin is designed by @olsonkundig and is located in Longbranch, Washington // Photos by @k7scott.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥

Swipe left! Dope or nope? 😍
Villa PR is a 50-year-old villa transformed into a comfortable, contemporary, and sustainable home. To maximise the enjoyment of the landscape, Villa RR has been extended with a glass volume at the western end – creating a strong connection between the interior and exterior environment. The transformation of the house is designed by Reitsema and Partners Archtitects and the house is located in Rijssen, Netherlands // Photos by Ronald Tilleman.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥

node.text:
Who’d you bring? 😍
The Dolomitenhütte is a mountain cabin situated in the Dolomites landscape where breathtaking views occur no matter which direction you look. Characterized by the surrounding mountains and forests, the mountain cabin is traditional yet modernized to take full advantage of the location. This mountain hut is located in Lienz, Austria // Video by @lumadeline.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥
Link in bio!

node.text:
Day or night? 🤔
New York City is well-known for its variety of architectural buildings. Some are traditional, some are more futuristic. In this case, an apartment building in Manhattan is kept to the bare minimum so that the interior do not take away any focus from the exterior cityscape. // Photos by @asya.rosh.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥

node.text:
The Ayvalaan House is a private home situated on a steep terrain making the home ideal for a multi-level layout. On the lower level, there is office space and family area. The intermediate level contains the living and dining section, whereas the top level concludes with the private floor. The house is designed by @paz_arquitectura and is located in Guatemala // Photos by @andresasturias.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥
Link in bio!

node.text:
Who’d love this cabin? 😍
Casa del Sapo is a unified home: a shelter, a safe space, a place where children can learn how to swim, where they can send turtles into the ocean, a place for friends, a place to eat and drink mezcal, a place to grow. In any way one can imagine, the home embraces your desires as two stones scouting the Pacific Ocean. It is designed by @espacio18 and is located on Zapotengo Beach in Oaxaca, Mexico // Photos by @onnisluque_fotografia.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥
Link in bio!

node.text:
How cool is this?! 😍
The King Bill Residence is designed as a “forever home” for a family of four. Situated in the back street of the vibrant Fitzroy neighborhood with rich nature, the house is playful with awesome design features while respectful to the heritage of the area. The house is designed by @austinmaynardarchitects and is located in Melbourne, Australia // Photos by @derek_swalwell.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥

Swipe left! What do you think? 💚
The Oak Pass Main House is a private single-family home with panoramic canyon views, lower level courtyard, infinity pool, and green roof among other things. The house is primarily built of structural concrete which enable the possibility of having long column free spans. The home is designed by Walker Workshop (@noah_walker) and is located in Beverly Hills, California // Photos by @joefletcherphoto.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥
